# Angular is front end framework which is used to develop single page applications

- Angular is based on MVC framework

# File and Folder structure in angular

1) package.json : All project related and dependencies present here
2) node modules : All liberies here
3) src folder : All actual code files
     i) app : All compoent files here
     ii) asset: public file for images and etc
     iii) Environment : All the environment related file testing, build. etc
     iv)  HTML file : All html code here
     v) main.js : This helps angular all js code in root file, main.js file will connect html with angular
     vi) style.css : Global css style
     

4) package-lock.json : 
5) angular.json : for application configuration, for folders and files
6) tscongig.json : Default configuration for typescript
7) tsconfigspec.json : for testing angular application
8) .browserlistsrc : All supported browser
9) karma.config.js : configuration for testing file
10) polyfill.ts :


# Interpolation in Angular

-Interpolation is used to display dynamic data on html page

-Interpolation can be used in app.component.html file

-we can not assaign value using interpolation


# Amgular CLI (Comman Line Interface)

1) ng help : Get list of all commands

2) add : Adds support for an external library to your project.
3) analytics : Configures the gathering of Angular CLI usage metrics. 
4) build (b) : Compiles an Angular app into an output directory named dist/ at the given output path. Must be executed from within a workspace directory.  

  deploy Invokes the deploy builder for a specified project or for the default project in the workspace.
  config Retrieves or sets Angular configuration values in the angular.json file for the workspace.
  doc (d) Opens the official Angular documentation (angular.io) in a browser, and searches for a given keyword.
  e2e (e) Builds and serves an Angular app, then runs end-to-end tests.       
  extract-i18n (i18n-extract, xi18n) Extracts i18n messages from source code. 
  
  Most Imp
  # generate (g) Generates and/or modifies files based on a schematic.

  help Lists available commands and their short descriptions.
  lint (l) Runs linting tools on Angular app code in a given project folder.  
  new (n) Creates a new workspace and an initial Angular application.
  run Runs an Architect target with an optional custom builder configuration defined in your project.
  serve (s) Builds and serves your app, rebuilding on file changes.
  test (t) Runs unit tests in a project.
  update Updates your application and its dependencies. See https://update.angular.io/
  version (v) Outputs Angular CLI version.


# Component in Angular 

- Component is building block of angular framework
- Component is re-usable in nature
- 

# Component with Inline Style and Inline Template

 There can be three cases :
  
   1) Component directly with the inline style 
   2) Component with inline template
   3) Component with inline style as well as inline template


   1) Component directly with the inline style :
      -Only theree files
      -No css file
      - CSS will be written inside ts file (i.e inline)
      - Used when we need to write only one or two line of css
   
   2) Component with inline template
      -Here dont have any html file 
      -we will just have css, spec and ts file
      -HTML will be written directly inside the ts file 
      -Used when we dont have HTML or we just have only one or two tag of html

   3) Component with inline style and inline html
      -both html and css written inisde ts file


# Modules in Angular

- Module is the complete feature of your angular application
- Module is nothing but the one of the feature of  your application (Important Feature)
- Multiple components, services, pipes, classes and interfeaces are comes under module
- Module is indepndent feature or functionality of your application
